{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "introduced Cycle GAN (CGAN) [26] to learn to translate images from source domain X to target domain Y without paired instances.",
    "Our goal is to develop a mapping G: X → Y that makes the distribution of images from G(X) indistinguishable from the distribution Y using an adversarial loss.",
    "The key is to grow both the generator and discriminator progressively from a low resolution.",
    "Dash et al.",
    "presented TAC-GAN [27] on the Oxford102 dataset of flowers and evaluated the discriminability of the generated images with Inception-Score and diversity with the Multi-Scale Structural Similarity Index (MS-SSIM)."
  ],
